title: Learn The Alphabet With Blippi | ABC Letter Boxes

json.text: Wow, look at this box!
It has a capital A on it and a lower case a on it.
Let’s open the box and see what’s inside!
An airplane, airplane starts with the later A.
Airplanes, airplanes flying way up high.
Some airplanes are big as a building, some are small as a car.
That’s amazing!
Some airplanes transport people, some flying near to the stars.
Wow! Look at this big blue box.
Big, blue and box all start with the letter B.
This is a capital B and that is a lowercase b.
Let’s open up the big blue box and see what’s inside!
Balls! Balls start with the letter B.
Wow.
Wow, and look at what else!
Boats. Boats start with the letter B.
Red boat, blue boat.
I saw a boat going faster and futher. I didn’t know the boats
so I asked my father. He said, “That’s a speed boat, son”.
I saw a boat fall of fishermen. I saw a boat full of business men.
I saw a boat…
Do you know what it was doing?
Oh, floating down the river.
Sailing on the sea.
Cruising on the ocean, boats are for me.
Wee-ha! Another letter of the alphabet
and this is letter is the letter C.
This is a capital C and that is a lowercase c.
I’m so excited to open up the box and see what’s inside!
A cement truck, cement start with the letter c. Cement truck.
Well, look at what it is. Another letter of the alphabet.
This letter is the letter D.
This is a capital D and that is a lowercase d.
Let’s open up the box and see what we can find
that starts with the letter D.
Yippi!
Oh, yeah, a dump truck. Wow!
It dumps stuff out of the back of the bed.
This is a dump truck.
Dump truck starts with the letter D.
Ooh, the letter E.
This is a capital E and that is a lowercase e.
Hum, I wonder what could be inside.
Probably something that starts with the letter E.
Let’s open it up and see!
Wow, an elephant!
Wow, these animals are so big!
I’m acting like an elephant!
Elephants are ginormous!
The heaviest elephant ever on record was about 24,000 lbs,
that’s about 11,000 kilograms.
To put it into perspective. Yeah, that’s about eight cars.
Wow, that’s heavy.
Ha, ha. Yes! Another box with the letter on it,
and this letter is the letter F.
This is a capital F and that is a lowercase f.
Hum, what do you think could be inside?
Probably something that starts with the letter F.
Ok, let’s open. Yeah.
Oh, yes!
Yeah, a fire truck. Fire truck start with the letter F.
Fire truck, fire truck, I wish I could ride a fire truck.
Fire truck, oh fire truck, I wish I could ride a fire truck.
I wish I could wake up in a fire station to the sound of fire bell.
I slide down the fire pole and go, wee-eeh!
All the way down, and hump on to the fire truck.
Fire truck, fire truck, I wish I could ride a fire truck.
Look at this green box.
Green, green starts with the letter G!
This is a capital G and that is a lowercase g.
Grass, grass, all that grass behind me starts with the letter G,
and it’s green!
Wow, so much G!
Let’s open up the box and see what’s inside.
Wow, woah.
Another thing that’s green. A garbage truck.
Garbage truck starts with the letter G.
Garbage trucks.
Garbage trucks.
Driven through the town, picking cans above the ground,
garbage trucks.
The garbage man drives up in the garbage truck
and takes that garbage up.
He dumps it in the back so that it can be crushed
but he drives off to the dump.
He backs up to a pile above the trash from the town
and dumps the whole thing out.
Garbage trucks.
Garbage trucks.
Driven through the town, picking cans above the ground,
garbage trucks.
Oh, look it here! Another box with the letter of the alphabet on it.
This box has the letter H.
This is a capital H and that is a lowercase h.
Let’s open the box and see what’s inside!
Oh, a helicopter!
Helicopter starts with the letter H.
Helicopters have some really funny nicknames!
Do you wanna hear some of them?
You can call them helos, whirlybirds,
copters and choppers!
Woo, another box! This box has the letter I on it.
This is a capital I and that is a lowercase i.
I wonder what’s inside.
Let’s open it up.
Yeah, yummy! Ice-cream!
I love ice-cream!
Mmm, yummy!
A box with the letter J on it.
I just jumped. Jump starts with the letter j.
This is a capital J and that is a lowercase j.
Huh, these are balls.
Ball, balls, none of those words start with the letter J.
But there is three of them.
Hum, what can we do that starts with the letter J.
Oh, I know!
Juggle!
Wee! Ha, ha, ha. I'm juggling three balls.
Juggle starts with the letter J.
Woo, look at what letter it is. It’s the letter K!
This is a capital K and this is a lowercase k.
Huh, another ball.
Ball does not start with the letter k either.
Huh, I wonder…
Oh, you know what we can do with the ball.
Yeah, we can kick the ball.
Ready?
Kick starts with the letter K.
Woo, another letter.
The word letter starts with the letter L.
This is a capital L and this is a lowercase l.
I wonder what’s inside!
Woah, huh...
A lime and a lemon.
Lime and lemon both start with the letter L.
I don’t have a knife or anything.
But, you know what I do have?
Are some of these!
This is gonna be fun!
Yeah, squash.
Wow, look at that. Yeah.
Let’s taste it, let’s taste the lime.
Woo, that’s strong!
Let’s try the lemon.
Alright.
Ok. Alright. There we go.
Alright, here we go!
That was fun!
And that is the inside of a lemon.
Let’s try the lemon.
Oh-oh, I’m scared.
Wow!
Humm, hummm, hummm, hummm.
This is the letter M.
This is a capital M and that is a lowercase m.
Let’s open it up and see what’s inside.
Monster truck.
Monster truck starts with the letter m.
Monster truck!
Monster trucks are big.
Monster trucks are loud.
Monster trucks jump high in the sky and they make such a monster sound.
Monster trucks are big.
Monster trucks are loud.
Monster trucks jump high in the sky and they make such a monster sound.
Oh-oh-oh, monster trucks in the air.
Oo-oh-oh, monster trucks in the dirt.
Oh-oh, can you hear the engine going so loud?
Woo, another box!
This box has the letter N on it.
This is a capital N and that is a lowercase n.
Hummm, let’s open up the box.
I love opening up the box and seeing what’s inside.
Woah, huh, two pieces of paper.
One says “No”, and one says, “Nice”.
Let’s talk about these words.
This word is nice,
nice is something you should be to other people.
Because if you’re nice to your friends and family and others
they are going to be nice back to you.
And if you are nice than you are gonna have tons of friends
and life is going to be dandy!
So, make sure you’re nice to people.
And then the word no. No, means no.
You say say no if there is ever anyone trying to get you do something
that you know you shouldn’t be doing.
Or if a stranger asks you to go with them or something like that.
Don’t go with strangers so you tell them, “No, no, no, no!”.
You can yell it as loud as you want. So no, means no.
This box has the letter O on it, and the box is orange
which starts with the letter O.
This is a capital O and that is a lowercase o.
My favourite part. I know I said that before
but we get to do it again. We get to open up the box.
Open starts with the letter O.
Oh, an orange, is the color orange. Orange starts with O,
and it’s an orange!
Hum, it’s hard to open.
Oh, I don’t have a knife or anything but, you know what I do got?
Cause I want some of this orange. I have… Yeah, alright.
Let’s put this right in there.
I’m ready. Ready?
Yeah, yeah. Ha, ha, ha.
Yes, look at that. Yummy orange!
Yumm.
Yumm, way better than the lime and the lemon.
Orange.
Wow, a purple box!
Purple starts with the letter P.
This is a capital P and that is a lowercase p.
Hummm, you know what time it is. Time to open the box.
Yeah, open the purple box with the letter P.
Wow, look at it!
Wow, police, police, police car.
Police car.
They drive really fast through the town.
They know my goodness their sirens are so loud.
Can you see they are red and blue lights?
Letting everybody know to let them by.
Police cars.
Police cars.
Police cars.
Wow, what interesting looking letters.
This is a capital Q and that is a lowercase q.
Hummm.
Can you tell what’s inside?
Can you hear it?
I think I know what’s inside that starts with the letter Q.
Yeah!
Wow.
Two quarters!
A quarter is a form of coin that's found in my currency
in United States of America which is where I live.
Wow, so these are coins
and the word quarter starts with the letter Q.
Woo, another box!
This box has the letter R on it.
This is a capital R and that is a lowercase r.
And what a coincidence!
This box is the color red and red starts with the letter R.
It’s time to open it up!
Red raspberries! Yumm.
I love raspberries.
Ooh, stay there red box.
Let’s taste some of these.
Yummy!
Have you ever had a raspberry before?
There are so tasty and delicious and they are good for you too
because is a fruit.
Those look like snakes, and those are the letter S.
Snake starts with the letter S.
This is a capital S and that is a lowercase s.
Let’s open it up. I hope there is not a snake inside.
That would be scary.
No snake, it’s a school bus!
Wow!
Let’s go to school, let’s go to school.
Let’s go to school. The school bus takes us to school.
The wheels on the bus go round and round, round and round,
round and round.
The wheels on the bus go round and round, all through the town.
The motor on the bus goes vroom, vroom, vroom,
vroom, vroom, vroom, vroom, vroom, vroom.
The motor on the bus goes vroom, vroom, vroom,
all through the town.
The doors on the bus go open and close, open and close,
open and close.
The doors on the bus go open and close, all through the town.
The wipers on the bus go whoosh, whoosh, whoosh,
whoosh, whoosh, whoosh, whoosh, whoosh, whoosh.
The wipers on the bus go whoosh, whoosh, whoosh,
all through the town.
Woo, an orange box!
Like the color of my suspenders, glasses, bow tie and part of my hat.
But anywho, this box has the letter T on it.
This is a capital T and that is a lowercase t.
Hummm.
Are you ready? Yeah.
Wow, yeah. A tractor!
Tractor starts with the letter T.
I know you like tractors.
And I love tractors!
Let’s go working on the farm, Let’s go working on the farm.
Oh tractor, oh tractor. Ha, ha, ha.
You know my tractor song.
Tractors, oh tractors.
Tractors, oh tractors, they are so much fun.
Tractors, oh tractors, they get the job done.
Tractors work all day.
Tractors work all night.
Got to bale that hay,
got to bale it tight.
They can be different colors,
green, red or blue.
Or yellow, or purple!
I wish I could drive one.
I wish I could too.
Tractors, oh tractors, they are so much fun.
Tractors, oh tractors, they get the job done.
The letter U! Ha, ha.
This is a capital U and that is a lowercase u.
Eew!
Undies! Underware!
Those weren’t mine.
The letter v.
This is a capital V and that is a lowercase v.
Shall we? I think we shall.
Oh, a carrot.
Carrot doesn’t start with the letter V.
But it is a vegetable.
Vegetable starts with the letter V.
Yumm, I love vegetables!
They are so good for you  and they will make you grow up
to be big and strong!
Oh, there is more vegetables.
Broccoli, yumm! I love broccoli!
Green onion!
V stands for vegetable.
Another box with the letter on it. Another box with the letter on it.
Another box with the letter on it, and this letter is W.
This is a capital W and that is a lowercase w.
I wonder what’s inside.
I can't hear anything.
A wheel loader.
Wheel loader starts with the letter W.
Well, look at what it is!
It is a the letter X.
This is a capital X, that is a lowercase x.
And look, something is poking out of the side already.
Must be really big.
Wow! Do you know what this is?
Watch this!
Yeah, this is a xylophone!
Listen.
Ok, I’ll play it for you.
I’m pretty good.
A yellow box!
Yellow starts with the letter Y!
This is a capital Y and that is a lowercase y.
A yoyo!
Have you ever seen one of this be played with before?
They’re really fun. I'm going to show you.
First you put the yoyo on your finger
and then you rap it around and then you through it down.
Woo, the last letter of the alphabet.
Yeap, it’s the letter Z.
This is a capital Z and that is a lowercase z.
The last box to open. Z.
A zebra!
Zebra starts with the letter Z.
I dropped the zebra.
Zebras kind of look like horses but they're all white with black stripes.
Well, that’s all folks.
That was sure fun learning all 26 letters of the alphabet with you.
Hey, if you want to watch more of my educational videos for kids,
all you’ve got to do is search for my name.
You know my name and now we can spell it because we know
all the letters of the alphabet!
Let’s spell it together.
B-L-I…
P-P-I-!
Blippi, that’s my name! Good job!
Alright, I’m gonna go play on the playground. Bye!
Parents, siblings, grandparents, babysitters!
I’d love for you to head over to my social media pages
like Facebook, Instagram and Twitter because I have fun news updates,
behind the scenes and even free merchandise giveaways!
Just search for my name, Blippi.
